        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>12CO(1-0) line of our target is located in Band 3. The two points that we plan to observe have the linewidth of 100 km/s (the central region of the galaxy) and ~30 km/s (the extraplanar gas), respectively. In order to resolve both regions kinematically, we aim to have at least 10 independent channels across ~30 km/s. Considering the sensitivity required to achieve our goal, the channel separation of 3 km/s will be a good compromise. The correlator mode of 1875 MHz width is the smallest possible bandwidth that can be set as standard mode for this observation, yet still provide an enough velocity coverage for this science. Spectral averaging of 2 will help to save the data rate while keeping our desired spectral resolution.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The goal is to resolve the overall distribution while keeping a high sensitivity. A resolution of 6 arcsec, ~twice the largest synthesized beam that can be reached with the 12m-array, will still give more than 50 spatial elements within a primary beam (note, we are imaging only several regions of a CO disk which is larger than the primary beam), which is enough to resolve the morphology but also allows us to achieve the sensitivity required for this science. Considering the CO extent (~12 arcsec) found in individual channels in our SMA observation, the most compact 12m configuration will be enough for this project.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Based on the previous single-dish 12CO(1-0) emission in the extraplanar gas (See Figure 2 in the Science Case), the estimated peak flux density per synthesized beam (~6 arcsec) of 12CO (1-0) line is 9.70 mJy. In order to resolve kinematics, we would like to have at least 10 independent elements over 30 km/s linewidth. With a channel of 3 km/s width, we should be able to image in 12CO(1-0) with S/N &gt; 3.7.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
