            <prj:justificationText>13CO(1-0) line of our target is located in Band 3. The two points that we plan to observe have the linewidth of 100 km/s (the central region of the galaxy) and ~30 km/s (the extraplanar gas), respectively. For 13CO which is expected to be fainter than 12CO, we do not attempt to resolve the kinematics but the detection is the goal, and we aim to have at least 3 independent channels across ~30 km/s. Considering the sensitivity required to achieve our goal, the channel separation of 10 km/s will be a good compromise. The correlator mode of 1875 MHz width is the smallest possible bandwidth that can be set as standard mode for this observation, yet still provide an enough velocity coverage for this science. Spectral averaging of 2 will help to save the data rate while keeping our desired spectral resolution.</prj:justificationText>
